Package: datacheckr
Title: Data Frame Column Name, Class and Value Checking
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: person("Joe", "Thorley", email = "joe@poissonconsulting.ca", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: The primary function check_data() checks a data frame for
    column presence, column class and column values.
    If the user-defined conditions are met the function
    returns the original data frame,
    otherwise the function throws an informative error. The package was written
    to provide a simple method for checking data frame
    inputs to functions that provides errors which allow end users
    to hopefully quickly identify and correct any problems with the data.
Depends:
    R (>= 3.2.3)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/poissonconsulting/datacheckr
LazyData: true
Suggests:
    assertr,
    magrittr,
    testthat,
RoxygenNote: 5.0.1
